|bio i am a huge stranger things fan i have bingewatched all seasons and episodes a couple of times and am patiently but impatiently waiting for other seasons here is some trivia about me: likes: computer programming drawing dancing singing sports video games (xbox and pc) bingewatching looking up at the sky and searching for cancellations and studying planets dislikes: slow internet cramps abuse and bullying and being ignored (especially on purpose) favorite seasons: summer and spring sometimes fall and winter because of halloween and christmas that is a summary of me thank you for visiting my page :) have a good day favorite characters will mike eleven (el) steve|

|the hawkins national laboratory seems to conduct unusual experiments" lends undue doubt to something we know to have happened prefer nonjudgmental language "martin brenner is pure evil" is a judgement by moral standards that are not shared by the entire readership verifiability {{shortcut|stw:ver}} verifiability on {{sitename}} is the readers ability to check [[stranger things wiki:citation|cited sources]] that directly support the information in an article all objective information in {{sitename}} must be verifiable but because other policies and guidelines also influence content verifiability does not guarantee inclusion verifiability and not truth is one of the fundamental requirements for inclusion in {{sitename}} truth of itself is not a substitute for meeting the verifiability requirement no matter how convinced you are that something is true do not add it unless it is verifiable information supported by actual broadcast episodes including captions are considered implicitly verified when (and only when) the episode is actually broadcast for the first time it must be possible to attribute all information in {{sitename}} to reliable published sources that are appropriate for the content in question however in practice it is only necessary to provide inline citations for quotations and for any information that has been challenged or that is likely to be challenged appropriate citations guarantee that the information is not [[original research|original research]] and allow readers and editors to check the source material for themselves any material that requires a citation but does not have one may be removed for help on adding citations see [[stranger things wiki:citation|citing sources]] this policy applies to all objective material in the mainspace (episode pages character pages location pages and production pages) in terms of spoilers and commentary pages text and pictures from articles may be copied into the site only if the work referenced has attribution for photos and images proper licensure and source is expected just being "out there on the internet" does not make a photo free to use on this wiki original research {{shortcut|stw:or}} the term "original research" (or) is used on {{sitename}} to refer to materialsuch as facts allegations and ideasfor which no reliable published sources exist this includes any analysis or synthesis of published material that serves to advance a position not advanced by the sources to demonstrate that you are not adding or you must be able to cite reliable published sources that are directly related to the topic of the article and directly support the material being presented (and as presented) the prohibition against or means that all material added to articles must be attributable to a reliable published source even if not actually attributed the verifiability policy says that an inline citation to a reliable source must be provided for all quotations and for anything challenged or likely to be challengedbut a source must exist even for material that is never challenged that "paris is the capital of france" needs no source because no one is likely to object to it and we know that sources exist for it the statement is attributable even if not attributed despite the need to attribute content to reliable sources you must not plagiarize them or violate their copyrights articles should be written in your own words while substantially retaining the meaning of the source material wikia policies there are very few policies which apply across all wikia these can be found on the central wikia at [[wikia:category:policy]] other policies for this wikia are usually decided by the wiki community in a consensus vote copyright except where otherwise specified the text on wikia sites is licensed under the creative commons attributionshare alike license 30 (unported) (ccbysa) [http://creativecommonsorg/licenses/bysa/30/ read the license summary] [http://creativecommonsorg/licenses/bysa/30/legalcode read the full legal code of the license] please see [[w:wikia:licensing|wikia:licensing]] for details __noeditsection__ |the article layout guide shows how articles should be structured and organized on the wiki this page will explain the organization of different types of articles as well as how to properly add content to each section character pages page layout character pages should more or less follow this layout: history background season personality relationships familial character name nonfamilial character name appearances memorable quotes behind the scenes trivia gallery references some of the sections included on the above list are optional some characters may even need additional sections depending on the information history here the characters actions throughout the series will be described all events excluding those that are included in the background subsection should be written in the order that they happened in the story all information should be recorded as it was presented in series no speculation or opinions should be present in this section the events should focus on the character whose page you are writing it for the events should also be written inuniverse and in past tense: correct: mike played dungeons & dragons with his friends in the basement incorrect: in the first episode mike is playing dungeons & dragons with his friends in the basement background this section consists of events that took place in the characters life before the start of the series events that are shown in flashbacks should be included in this section for some pages this subsection may be divided into different sections for example elevens background is split into birth and early life and psychokinetic training some characters may not have this subsection due to there being no information about their past season here is where the events that took place in the current timeline of the story this section is usually what takes up a majority of the article be descriptive dont overly summarize events make sure to include all events even if the character only appeared in the background in a scene it should be included personality here the qualities of the characters personality will be described this section may sometimes be called personality and traits its not enough to just say a character is brave give some examples of the characters bravery the characters likes and dislikes can be noted here any other traits characteristics and mannerisms can also go here relationships here is where the characters relationships will be described basically summarize the characters interactions this section usually has two subsections: familial this can also include adopted and surrogate relationships nonfamilial this includes all other relationships that are not part of the characters family friends romantic interests enemies and other relationships should go here the relationships should be written mostly from the perspective of the character youre writing it for only notable relationships should be described here while holly wheeler is mikes sister not much has been shown of them interacting so holly should not be included in this section on mikes page one common problem with writing this section is that some interactions between characters may have different meanings and interpretations to other people as a result it is sometimes easy to get carried away with personal opinions please avoid this as much as possible and instead focus on how the characters relationships were meant to be depicted in the story if at any point this section becomes too lengthy then it should be moved to a separate page appearances this is where the characters episode appearances are noted usually this section only consists of the season appearance templates for more information please view the templates section below memorable quotes here notable things said by the character will be listed the quotes should be placed with bullet points and have quotations marks the quotes should be important and have impact fanfavorite lines can go here behind the scenes behind the scenes is a section for "realworld" facts facts about casting and the characters creation should be written here this section should be written in paragraphs not bullet points also it should not be written from an inuniverse point of view trivia trivia is a collection of interesting often little known facts about the character all facts should be written in bullet points this section can include: observations made about the character by observing background clues or hints present in dialogue facts revealed about the character in interviews or any other official source acknowledgment of fan reactions and fan theories this section is also one of the few sections where speculation is somewhat acceptable as long as it is made clear that it has not been confirmed gallery galleries are to display interesting images in this case the gallery will display images of the character during interesting or major situations the basic code for a gallery:|

a list of the cast and their characters along with how many episodes they appear in in bullet point form main cast all major cast members and their characters recurring cast recurring cast members and their characters episodes the seasons episodes displayed in a table the table should include an image from each episode as well as each episodes title director(s) writers and synopsis development anything relating to the development of the season such as conception crew and casting each aspect of development should be its own subsection subsections may vary production anything relating to the production of the season such as filming and special effects filming any details about the seasons filming such as schedules and filming of particular scenes special effects any details about how the seasons sfx were accomplished music details about the music used in the season can include details about both the original score as well as the soundtrack postproduction any details involving postproduction such as editing marketing advertising for the season this section mainly consists of the seasons trailers other pages while all other page types on the wiki dont have specific layouts that should be followed it is important that they still follow the wikis guidelines and maintain a certain level of consistency minor pages multiple subjects such as characters locations etc that alone do not have enough information for their own article can be combined into one article on these pages subjects will be listed alphabetically and each have their own section an image of the subject should be displayed on the right the template should be placed at the end of each section to ensure that images dont overlap into another section categories and templates for these pages will vary but should correspond to the subjects listed location pages the infobox should be used depending on the type of location there may be a list of inhabitants staff students etc there may also be a profile listing all of the locations known rooms and areas location pages should be placed in [[:category:locations]] and any appropriate subcategories cast pages for cast pages the infobox should be used the article introduction will consist of a summary of the cast members career be respectful when adding information cast pages should be placed in category:cast subcategories will depend on the season(s) the cast member appeared in filmography a list of media the cast member has worked on over their career displayed on a table may sometimes be divided into subsections such as film television etc crew pages director producer and writer pages will all use the infobox depending on the crew member they should be placed in the [[:category:directors|directors]] [[:category:producers|producers]] and/or [[:category:writers|writers]] categories credits a list of the crew members directing/producing/writing credits throughout the series|

|it is highly possible that an article has far too many images that they overshadow the significance of the article the editors here should strive for a tasteful array rather than a garish smorgasbord of images such displays should be curated to the most significant impactful or best images either that or they must be arranged and organized in a better manner than the current gallery slideshow or table (or lack of these elements) provides this can even apply to media subpages just because they are in the right place doesnt mean they should be disorganized naming {{shortcut|stw:filename}} when uploading or embedding a media file it is good practice to name the file something significant so that it is easy to find later images : screencaps should use "file:s01e01 description" format where possible admins are able to rename items in the file: namespace if you upload a lot of material and your file: names do not conform to this policy you will be directed to this page :other than screencaps: aim for being descriptive where possible videos :"video:teaser s01e99" is the preferred format for directly episode related material and whatever description is appropriate put the episode number in front if its a scene from the episode but after if its a video about an episode this makes finding them later much easier keep in mind that you cant use the "" mark in the title and use of punctuation should be avoided in the title examples of good names : video:teaser s01e14 video:sneak preview s01e15 video:s01e06 jonathan and nancy video:bts ctreature makeup examples of bad names : video:see a sneak preview of the thirteenth episode of stranger things video:stranger things on netflix the duffer brothers talk about their show stranger things to a reporter categories and as you might expect: categories file: and video: items have their own pages for description metadata license etc they can also be placed into categories and should be quotations {{shortcut|stw:quote}} quotations help to liven up a page using dialogue from characters to help "set the scene" of a section so to speak quotations are created through the use of quotation templates (namely {{tl|dialogue}} and {{tl|line}}) an overuse of quotes can make an article look very sloppy this is particularly enforced on good articles and featured articles category these should only be applied if one can actually say something relevant about all members of the group as a generalization in the category:students example there are things that can be said about the entirety of the members (the rules and mythology of ghosts in this shows paradigm) the same cant be said of all male vs female characters ditto main vs recurring vs guest overorganization can become an easy compulsion to follow adding categories like "sex" and "teen angst" to a page 30 at a time is also not very helpful articles are not like blog posts where they require as many tags as possible the category system was not designed to be used as thematic tags like keywords and is primarily for housekeeping article management and site navigation the extraneous tags make administration and navigation more difficult getting help following these guidelines may seem like a daunting task for users who are new to wikis and the encyclopedic format we understand that and it is perfectly normal that some people may be confused to ease this confusion the admins and many contributors are very willing to help anyone who needs it and asks for it that last point asking for it is very important because we have no way of knowing if you want help unless you seek it __noeditsection__ [[category:guidelines]][[category:community]]|

|the purpose of this page is to serve as a guide for new contributors to the wiki this way the wiki will run more smoothly and look more polished for the purposes of this guide it will be assumed that whoevers reading it at least knows the basics of editing if not there are plenty of [[community:help:tutorial|tutorials]] available over at [[community:community_central|community central]] asking more experienced users as well as the wikis staff is also a good way to learn page layout the usual layout for a character page should be like this: introduction history background (optional) season personality relationships (may be a separate article) family friends enemies other appearances memorable quotes behind the scenes (optional) trivia (optional) gallery (may be a separate page) references (optional but preferred) please keep in mind that this is the usual layout for a character page pages about locations items etc may have different layouts introduction the articles introduction is basically what introduces the reader to the subject a good way to write this section is to summarize the subjects storyline throughout the series history while you summarized the subjects role in the introduction here you will go into more detail this section will usually be the majority of the article background|

|the purpose of this page is to serve as a guide for new contributors to the wiki this way the wiki will run more smoothly and look more polished for the purposes of this guide it will be assumed that whoevers reading it at least knows the basics of editing if not there are plenty of [[community:help:tutorial|tutorials]] available over at [[community:community_central|community central]] asking more experienced users as well as the wikis staff is also a good way to learn articles content: one majority of the wikis content will simply be derived from the source material while the other majority will be from interviews and other official statements from the cast and crew any information on this wiki must be verifiable and come from official sources those sources must be cited all information must be officially revealed no information from leaks or untrustworthy sources will be permitted on the wiki this wiki focuses on canon this is not a place for fanon content with the only exception being for use on user profiles speculation theories or opinions should be absent from main article sections if something is ambiguous in the series then it should be ambiguous on the wiki minimal speculation should only be applied when it is necessary and must be somewhat supported by hints present in canon writing: keep in mind when writing for articles that the main purpose is to record information the writing should be comprehensible but not too overly complicated or fancy formal language should be used avoid using any slang or overly casual tones articles should be written from a neutral point of view (npov) even when writing for antagonists or describing events that could be seen as malicious please avoid simply tacking sentences on to the ends of paragraphs instead try to integrate the sentence where it belongs in the paragraph or even rewrite the paragraph to include the information tense: episode pages should be written in present tense character pages as well as most other pages should be written in past tense exceptions to this are trivia sections and any other section where present tense is necessary citing sources sources are extremely important to the wiki they let readers know that the information they are getting is confirmed and reliable references must come from reliable sources reliable sources can include: official interviews with the cast and crew posts made by any of the shows official social media accounts posts made by any of the cast and crews social media accounts videos posted by the official netflix youtube channel or other credible channels videos of the cast at comic con panels (while posted by unofficial sources they still contain official statements) when citing a reference the content must be place between tags for example: it is extremely important that the reference links to the original source they should also have the name of the website where the source was published as well as the date it was published a typical reference should follow this format:|

|the style guide explains the basic guidelines for creating and adding content to articles this way information on the wiki will be more consistent and organized for article organization and adding content to specific sections please see the article layout guide please keep in mind that some of the policies on this page may change articles content: one majority of the wikis content will simply be derived from the source material while the other majority will be from interviews and other official statements from the cast and crew any information on this wiki must be verifiable and come from official sources those sources must be cited all information must be officially revealed no information from leaks or untrustworthy sources will be permitted on the wiki this wiki focuses on canon this is not a place for fanon content with the only exception being for use on user profiles speculation theories or opinions should be absent from main article sections if something is ambiguous in the series then it should be ambiguous on the wiki minimal speculation should only be applied when it is necessary and must be somewhat supported by hints present in canon writing: keep in mind when writing for articles that the main purpose is to record information the writing should be comprehensible but not too overly complicated or fancy formal language should be used avoid using any slang or overly casual tones articles should be written from a neutral point of view (npov) even when writing for antagonists or describing acts that could be seen as malicious please avoid simply tacking sentences on to the ends of paragraphs instead try to integrate the sentence where it belongs in the paragraph or even rewrite the paragraph to include the information tense: episode pages should be written in present tense character pages as well as most other pages should be written in past tense exceptions to this are trivia sections and any other section where present tense is necessary spelling and terminology: this wiki allows both american and british spelling however because this is an american made show the american spelling for some words will potentially be more common american terminology should be used when referring to objects especially if they are addressed as such in the show text formatting bold bold text will be used in article introductions where the subjects name or its equivalent will be bold if an article has numerous sections and subsections bold text can be used to help readers distinguish between sections italics italics should be used when naming a piece of media films books and even the shows title itself should be italicized parts of character quotes can also be italicized for emphasis naming pages capitalization: when naming pages this wiki uses [https://enwiktionaryorg/wiki/sentence_case sentence case] exceptions to this are character names episode titles and any other official titles character pages: when naming character pages any titles and honorifics should be absent if a characters first name has not been given then the page should use their surname some character articles will be named after what the character is mostly known by or what they mostly refer to themselves as while mikes real name is micheal his page is named mike wheeler because that is what he refers to himself as as well as what most people call him elevens page is not named jane ives or jane eleven ives because she has no knowledge of that name similar names: if multiple subjects have similar names each page should be given a different title from the primary topic placing the distinguishing title in parenthesis the page about the shows alternate dimension is titled [[the upside down]] while the page regarding the episode is named [[the upside down (episode)]] unnamed subjects: sometimes a subject may go unnamed in the show in these cases either the most appropriate name should be given or a name should be agreed upon by the community a notice should also be placed at the top of the page to notify both readers and editors that the name is nonofficial and subject to change citing sources sources are extremely important to the wiki they let readers know that the information they are getting is confirmed and reliable references must come from reliable sources reliable sources can include: episodes official interviews with the cast and crew posts made by any of the shows official social media accounts posts made by any of the cast and crews social media accounts videos posted by the official netflix youtube channel or other credible channels videos of the cast at comic con panels (while posted by unofficial sources they still contain official statements) when citing a reference the content must be placed between tags for example: it is extremely important that the reference links to the original source they should also have the name of the website where the source was published as well as the date it was published a typical reference should follow this format: when or when not to create an article while its true that the wikis purpose is to be a place to house and obtain information its important to remember that this is the stranger things wiki all articles on this wiki must be related and relevant to [[stranger things]] however that does not mean that every single character or item mentioned in the series is necessarily important enough to get their own page the series also often has references to reallife people and media especially those that inspired it while these references are interesting and should definitely be mentioned that doesnt mean they warrant their own article relevancy: this will be the main factor when figuring out if a subject should have its own page was the subject relevant to the show/story? did it play a major role or was it just mentioned in a passing line of dialogue? the [[sensory deprivation tank]] deserves its own article because it played a vital role in the story it was how eleven entered her mental void where she made contact with the monster opening the rift to the upside down meanwhile the [[atari]] doesnt get its own article because it was only mentioned and not important to the story information: is there enough information on the subject to warrant an article? if only two or three sentences can be written about the subject odds are it shouldnt have an article integration: while the subject may not require its own article that doesnt mean it shouldnt be mentioned at all if the subject is related to another bigger more important topic then it can be integrated somewhere on that topics article either as its own section or a subsection combination: sometimes if there are multiple similar subjects that alone do not have enough information they can be combined into a single article|

|tense in order to maintain some style and consistency across articles we should have a set standard on which tense they should be written in there is a tiny little mention in the mos about this but its not really official (or entirely clear for that matter) i think the community needs to agree to a standard and stick to it i think articles about things that exist "inside" the shows universe (characters locations events etc) should be written in the past tense were writing about events from 1983 after all writing in the present tense reads like a plot summary and reading about the history of a person or thing as if it is happening in real time is not customary and feels very strange [[user:80xpd|80xpd]] ([[user talk:80xpd|talk]]) 21:25 september 7 2016 (utc)|

|tense in order to maintain some style and consistency across articles we should have a set standard on which tense they should be written in there is a tiny little mention in the mos about this but its not really official (or entirely clear for that matter) i think the community needs to agree to a standard and stick to it i think articles about things that exist "inside" the shows universe (characters locations events etc) should be written in the past tense were writing about events from 1983 after all writing in the present tense reads like a plot summary and reading about the history of a person or thing as if it is happening in real time is not customary and feels very strange [[user:80xpd|80xpd]] ([[user talk:80xpd|talk]]) 21:25 september 7 2016 (utc) i have a rough draft of what i believe the basic layout for pages about characters creatures locations or objects on this wiki should be this is not a definite layout only a suggestion ive included some of the things already written under the layout guide section of this page some pages will require more sections and others will not need every section listed here again this is only a suggestion and needs the input of other wiki users infobox banners introduction history this section shows the history of the topic of the article in stranger things all sections under this heading should be written from an inuniverse point of view and in pasttense background the background of a character location creature or object before the events of stranger things that occur in "presenttime" events that occurred in flachbacks are written here season one occurrences pertaining to the topic of the article that happened during season one of stranger things are written here trivia trivia is a collection of random facts about a character creature location or object this section should be written using bullet points all facts in this section are inuniverse trivia is not to be confused with behind the scenes behind the scenes behind the scenes is a section for "realworld" facts facts about casting or filming locations should be written here this section should be written in paragraphs not bullet points also it should not be written from an inuniverse point of view [[user:highspeednerd|highspeednerd]] ([[user talk:highspeednerd|talk]]) 00:33 october 17 2016 (utc)highspeednerd|

|{{tlc|about}} is a commonly used [[wikipedia:wp:hatnote|hatnote template]] on wikipedia and should be placed at the top of an article linking the reader to other articles with similar titles or concepts that they may have been seeking instead the template has several formats including: {{tlx|about|use1}} → {{about|use1}} {{tlx|about|use1||page2}} → {{about|use1||page2}} {{tlx|about|use1|use2|page2}} → {{about|use1|use2|page2}} {{tlx|about|use1|use2|page2|and|page3}} → {{about|use1|use2|page2|and|page3}} {{tlx|about|use1|use2|page2|other uses}} → {{about|use1|use2|page2|other uses}} alternately a parameter can be added to the {{tlc|about}} template for use at the top of a section when using this parameter the wording in the template changes to specify that it is being used in a section: {{tlx|about|use1|}} → {{about|use1|sectionyes}} {{tlx|about|use1|}} → {{about|use1||page2|sectionyes}} {{tlx|about|use1|use2|page2|}} → {{about|use1|use2|page2|sectionyes}} {{tlx|about|use1|use2|page2|and|page3|}} → {{about|use1|use2|page2|and|page3|sectionyes}} {{tlx|about|use1|use2|page2|other uses|}} → {{about|use1|use2|page2|other uses|sectionyes}} for more options find "{{tlf|about}}" in the text below for reference see [[wikipedia:wikipedia:hatnote|hatnote]] and documentation below {{hatnote templates}} [[category:disambiguation and redirection templates]] [[category:hatnote templates]]|

|this template can be used on user and user talk pages to display an image that will remain in the same position even when the page is scrolled parameters: one unnamed parameter the only required one if the image is uploaded to this wiki use the file name otherwise use a direct url to the image and use the is not working) top the distance (in px) between the image and the top of the page right the distance (in px) between the image and the right side of the page bottom the distance (in px) between the image and the bottom of the page left the distance (in px) between the image and the left side of the page size allows you to resize the image defaults to full size can be specified by width or height you can hide all images that use this template by adding the following to [[special:mypage/commoncss|your css]]: fixedimagetemplate {display:none} you can make all such images hideable on click by adding the following to [[special:mypage/commonjs|your javascript]]: //removing fixed images on click $("fixedimagetemplate")click(function () { $(this)hide(500 function () { $(this)remove() }) })|

|this template produces formatted text following the guideline for a [[wp:hatnote|hatnote]] : {{hatnote|example hatnote text}} broadly speaking a hatnote should answer a readers question (maybe preemptively): am i on the right page? function this template is primarily used to add a correctly formatted hatnote to a page often but not always this is a disambiguation link at the top of article pages it places an html block around the text entered as its only argument which provides standardized formatting (contents are indented and italicized in most displays) it also isolates the contained code to make sure that it is interpreted correctly this template is also used as the "metatemplate" for additional specialized disambiguation link templates see [[:category:hatnote templates]] for a list the template does not automatically create links of any kind links and other desired formatting must be explicitly added using normal [[help:wikitext|markup]] usage basic usage: &123{hatnote|text}} all parameters: &123{hatnote|text|extraclassesextra classes|selfrefyes|categoryno}} parameters this template accepts the following parameters: the hatnote text (required) any extra css classes to be added for example the {{t|see also}} template adds the classes boilerplate seealso if set to "yes" "y" "true" or "1" adds the css class "selfref" this is used to denote selfreferences if set to "no" "n" "false" or "0" suppresses the error tracking category ([[:category:hatnote templates with errors]]) this only has an effect if the first positional parameter (the hatnote text) is omitted example → {{hatnote|example hatnote text}} errors if no hatnote text is supplied the template will output the following message: {{hatnote|categoryno}} if you see this error message it is for one of four reasons: no parameters were specified (the template code was instead some parameters were specified but the hatnote text wasnt included for example the template text instead the hatnote text was specified but that text contains an equals sign ("") the equals sign has a special meaning in template code and because of this it cannot be used in template parameters that do not specify a parameter name for example the template code you tried to access [[module:hatnote]] directly by using instead if you see this error message and are unsure of what to do please post a message on [[template talk:hatnote]] and someone should be able to help you pages that contain this error message are tracked in [[:category:hatnote templates with errors]] technical details the html code produced by this template looks like this: the code is produced by [[module:hatnote]] {{ifeq:{{subpagename}}|sandbox|| [[category:hatnote templates| ]] [[category:crossreference templates]] }}|

|{{headermain|textabout stranger things|size30|barwidth469}} [[file:stranger things art poster 002jpg|right|150px|linkstranger things]]{{st}} is an american supernatural science fiction horror web television series created by the duffer brothers for netflix it was written and directed by matt and ross duffer and executiveproduced by shawn levy on november 6 1983 in indiana 12yearold will byers vanishes instantly wills mother joyce becomes frantic and tries to find will while police chief hopper begins his own investigation the very next day a mysterious girl with strange abilities appears who knows the whereabouts of will but as they get closer to the truth they will have to face not only a sinister government agency but a more insidious force who plans on devouring them all|

|{{headermain|textabout stranger things|size30|barwidth469}} [[file:stranger things art poster 002jpg|right|150px|linkstranger things]]{{st}} is an american supernatural science fiction horror web television series created by the duffer brothers for netflix it was written and directed by matt and ross duffer and executiveproduced by shawn levy this thrilling netflixoriginal drama stars awardwinning actress winona ryder as joyce byers who lives in a small indiana town in 1983 inspired by a time when tales of science fiction captivated audiences when joyce byers 12yearold son will goes missing she launches a terrifying investigation into his disappearance with local authorities as they search for answers they unravel a series of extraordinary mysteries involving secret government experiments unnerving supernatural forces and a very unusual little girl|

|{{headermain|textfeatured article|size30|barwidth355}} {{headermain|right|text[[demogorgon (species)|demogorgon (species)]]|size23|barwidth0}}[[file:demogorgon chapter eightjpg|left|190px|linkdemogorgon (species)]]demogorgons are predatory creatures originating from the [[upside down]] an alternate dimension demogorgons obey the malicious [[mind flayer]] and make up part of his hive mind under his influence demogorgons are murderous violent and have limited intelligence in 1983 a [[the demogorgon|fully grown demogorgon]] set foot in [[hawkins]] indiana after a [[gate|gateway]] to the upside down was accidentally opened this demogorgon was eventually defeated and destroyed but not before it could inflict damage upon the human world [[will byers]] a rescued victim of the demogorgon became a vessel for the mind flayer somehow wills possession allowed the mind flayer to unleash a swarm of adolescent demogorgons upon hawkins {{center|[[demogorgon (species)|]]}} [[category:main page templates]]|

|{{headermain|textfeatured article|size30|barwidth355}} {{headermain|right|text[[the upside down|the upside down]]|size23|barwidth0}}[[file:upsidedowns2png|left|210px|linkthe upside down]]the upside down is an alternate dimension existing in parallel to the human world most if not all flora and fauna present in the dimension are linked together in a hive mind controlled by the [[mind flayer]] essentially forming an enormous superorganism a key component of this hive mind was a species of humanoid predators dubbed [[demogorgon (species)|demogorgons]] which originated from the dimension {{center|[[the upside down|]]}} [[category:main page templates]]|

|{{headermain|textfeatured article|size30|barwidth355}} {{textcolor|red|w}}{{textcolor|orange|i}}{{textcolor|yellow|l}}{{textcolor|green|l}} {{textcolor|blue|b}}{{textcolor|violet|y}}{{textcolor|red|e}}{{textcolor|orange|r}}{{textcolor|yellow|s}} [[file:will s2png|left|170px|linkwill byers]]william "will" byers portrayed by [[noah schnapp]] is a recurring character in the [[season 1|first season]] of [[stranger things]] and a main character in the [[season 2|second season]] on the night of november 6th 1983 will was abducted by the [[demogorgon]] and taken into an alternate dimension dubbed the [[upside down]] for a week will evaded the creature while his family and friends desperately searched for him although he was eventually rescued and returned to normal life his time in the upside down left him with a mysterious connection to the alternate realm {{center|[[will byers|]]}} [[category:main page templates]]|

|{{headermain|textfeatured article|size30|barwidth355}} {{textcolor|red|w}}{{textcolor|orange|i}}{{textcolor|yellow|l}}{{textcolor|green|l}} {{textcolor|blue|b}}{{textcolor|violet|y}}{{textcolor|red|e}}{{textcolor|orange|r}}{{textcolor|yellow|s}} [[file:will s2png|left|170px|linkwill byers]]william "will" byers portrayed by [[noah schnapp]] is a recurring character in the [[season 1|first season]] of [[stranger things]] and a main character in the [[season 2|second season]] on the night of november 6th 1983 will was abducted by the [[demogorgon]] and taken into an alternate dimension dubbed the [[upside down]] for a week will evaded the creature while his family and friends desperately searched for him although he was eventually rescued and returned to normal life his time in the upside down left him with a mysterious connection to the alternate realm {{center|[[will byers|]]}} [[category:main page templates]]|

|{{headermain|textfeatured article|size30|barwidth355}} {{headermain|text[[will byers|will byers]]|size23|barwidth0}} [[file:will s2png|left|170px|linkwill byers]]william "will" byers portrayed by [[noah schnapp]] is a recurring character in the [[season 1|first season]] of [[stranger things]] and a main character in the [[season 2|second season]] on the night of november 6th 1983 will was abducted by the [[demogorgon]] and taken into an alternate dimension dubbed the [[upside down]] for a week will evaded the creature while his family and friends desperately searched for him although he was eventually rescued and returned to normal life his time in the upside down left him with a mysterious connection to the alternate realm {{center|[[will byers|]]}} [[category:main page templates]]|

|{{headermain|textfeatured article|size30|barwidth355}} {{headermain|text[[the void|the void]]|size23|barwidth0}} [[file:stranger things 1x06elevens mental voidjpg|left|200px|linkthe void]]the void is a visual representation of [[eleven]]s mind while using extrasensory perception to locate other entities in different locations to her own the void appears as a vast endless expanse of nothingness the floor is covered in a thin layer of water it is completely empty not including eleven herself or whatever or whoever she is trying to locate {{center|[[the void|]]}} [[category:main page templates]]|

|{{headermain|textfeatured article|size30|barwidth355}} {{headermain|text[[the vanishing of will byers|the vanishing of will byers]]|size23|barwidth0}} [[file:the vanishing of will byers s01e01 ss 001png|left|260px|linkthe vanishing of will byers]]"chapter one: the vanishing of will byers" is the first episode of [[stranger things|stranger things]] and the first episode of the [[stranger things/season 1|first season]] it was written and directed by the [[the duffer brothers|duffer brothers]] and premiered on [[netflix]] on july 15 2016 along with the rest of the season on his way home from a [[mike wheeler|friend]]s house young [[will byers|will]] sees [[the monster|something terrifying]] nearby a [[gate|sinister secret]] lurks in the depths of a [[hawkins national laboratory|government lab]] {{center|[[the vanishing of will byers|]]}} [[category:main page templates]]|

|{{headermain|textfeatured article|size30|barwidth355}} {{headermain|text[[the key|the key]]|size23|barwidth0}} [[file:starcourt key machinepng|left|250px|linkthe key]] "the key" referred to a type of russian machine that could open [[portals|gates]] to the [[upside down]] though the term "key" was also colloquially used to refer to the gates themselves when activated using two special keys the machine fired a highpowered laser beam which could open "a doorway between worlds" {{center|[[the key|]]}} [[category:main page templates]]|

|when an article is large it is often written in summary style this template is used after the heading of the summary to link to the subtopic article that has been summarized this template should not be used in lead sections a lead section is always a summary of its own article not any other as such the only appropriate target for a {{t|main}} link in the lead section would be the article itself which is not useful usage basic usage: {{t|main|page}} all parameters: | page1 | page2 | page3 | | l1 label1 | l2 label2 | l3 label3 | | selfref yes parameters the pages to link to if no page names are specified the current page name is used instead (without the namespace prefix) categories and files are automatically escaped with the [[help:colon trick|colon trick]] and links to sections are automatically formatted as page § section rather than the mediawiki default of pagesection for this template does not work) namespace pages errors if the name of the first page that you want to link to is not specified the current page name (with no namespace prefix) is used instead no errors can be displayed due to the illegal usage of parameters or other usages (ie the first parameter can be omitted other parameters can be used even if the first one is empty (and automatically filled with the current page name (with no namespace prefix)) equals sign can be used as one of the parameters and template can be used by direct call to the module (using "invoke")) this is not case for {{t|see also}} for example {{ifeq:{{subpagename}}|sandbox|| [[category:crossreference templates]] [[category:exclude in print]] [[category:hatnote templates]] [[category:list templates]] }}|

|while benny is doing dishes eleven is feeding the rottweiler fish the dog licks her face causing her to smile benny remarks that a smile looks good on her and eleven calls him good in return he states he knows a few people who would disagree and reveals a list of tattooed names on his arm most likely belonging to his exgirlfriends eleven points to a name reading tommy saying it belongs to his little brother benny is confused but before he can question further he hears someone arrive in the driveway a woman named [[connie frazier]] is at the door after saying she is from social services benny lets her in connie shoots benny and agents swarm the restaurant in the kitchen agent one kills the dog when it attempts to attack him suddenly eleven blasts the storage closet door open injuring the agents in the process she laments bennys and the dogs deaths calls the agents bad and then flees act five at the bonfire nancy and barb are waiting for steve he finally shows up but appears to be drunk and stoned he leads nancy away leaving barb behind meanwhile mike lucas and dustin meet and set off for mirkwood steve leads nancy to a more secluded part of the beach he pushes her down and begins removing her clothing nancy is hesitant towards steves advances but he continues anyway back at the bonfire barb gets tired of waiting for nancy and decides to leave after starting her car the radio cycles through various stations playing garbled distorted noise and the cars lights flicker confused barb turns the engine off a moment later the back window shatters the cars lights turn on and a highpitched sound is heard once the sound has faded and the lights have dimmed barb is gone when jonathan arrives home joyce is working on wills missing poster they are consoling each other when the phone rings joyce answers it but only hears the sound of someones breathing she repeatedly asks who it is with the breathing only growing louder at last a distant voice belonging to will responds joyce frantically asks where he is but his voice is replaced with a new inhuman one a highpitched sound emits from the receiver joyce drops the phone her palm now seared jonathan quickly grabs the phone but the line is now dead a distant voice calls for help barbara stumbles onto the beach her nose and ears bleeding the beach is empty but she can still hear the distant sounds of the bonfire there is a thick fog and the waves seem to roll in slowly like time is distorted there are pulsating growths all over the sand and blue lightning flashes in the sky barb hears guttural sounds coming from behind her she turns to see a horde of shadowed figures heading towards her the boys are searching for will on mirkwood when mike sees a figure in the middle of the road he tries to avoid it causing lucas and dustin to crash into him once hes back on his feet mike shines his flashlight on the figure revealing it to be eleven a rumbling sound is heard from overhead making mike look up at the sky joyce jonathan and hopper are looking up too dark silhouetted clouds roll in above the town and blue lightning illuminates the sky the script ends ominously saying the storm is no longer coming its here }}|

|this template is used to create hatnotes to point to a small number of other related titles at the top of [[help:section|article sections]] it looks like this: {{see also|article}} do not use this template inside the "see also" section at the end of an article or for links to other articles or subsections of the same article within regular article text where subsections are linked to {{t|section link}} may be suitable instead refer to the examples below to see how the template handles link targets containing section links and commas usage basic usage: &123{see also|page1|page2|page3|}} all parameters: &123{see also | page1 | page2 | page3 | | label 1 label 1 | label 2 label2 | label 3 label3 | | l1 label1 | l2 label2 | l3 label3 | | selfref yes | category no }} parameters this template accepts the following parameters: the pages to link to at least one page name is required categories and files are automatically escaped with the [[help:colon trick|colon trick]] and links to sections are automatically formatted as page § section rather than the mediawiki default of pagesection optional labels for each of the pages to link to if set to "yes" "y" "true" or "1" adds the css class "selfref" this is used to denote selfreferences if set to "no" "n" "false" or "0" suppresses the error tracking category ([[:category:hatnote templates with errors]]) this only has an effect if the first positional parameter (the page to link to) is omitted examples → {{see also|article}} → {{see also|articlesection}} → {{see also|articlesection|label 1custom section label}} → {{see also|article1|article2|article3}} → {{see also|article1|article2|article3}} → {{see also|article1|l1custom label 1|article2|l2custom label 2}} → {{see also|veni vidi vici|julius caesar}} → {{see also|veni vidi vici|julius caesarcivil war}} → {{see also|julius caesarcivil war|veni vidi vici}} → {{see also|julius caesarcivil war|crossing the rubicon}} errors if no page names are supplied the template will output the following message: {{see also|categoryno}} if you see this error message it is for one of four reasons: no parameters were specified (the template code was instead some parameters were specified but no page names were included for example the template text instead a page name was specified but it contains an equals sign ("") the equals sign has a special meaning in template code and because of this it cannot be used in template parameters that do not specify a parameter name for example the template code you tried to access [[module:see also]] directly by using instead pages that contain this error message are tracked in [[:category:hatnote templates with errors]] see also {{t|main}} {{ifeq:{{subpagename}}|sandbox|| [[category:list templates]] [[category:exclude in print]] [[category:hatnote templates]] [[category:relatedtopic templates]] [[category:crossreference templates]] }}|

|{{headermain |text user guidelines |size 60 |barwidth 450 }} this page outlines the basic guidelines that users must follow while active on the stranger things wiki please be aware that in addition to the guidelines on this page users must also follow fandom’s [https://wwwfandomcom/termsofuse terms of use] any questions should be directed toward the [[stranger things wiki:staff|wikis staff]] basic guidelines in compliance with the terms of use users must be at least 13 years of age in order to create an account and contribute to this wiki if you reside in the european economic area (excluding the uk) then you must be at least 16 years old always assume good faith assume that all edits are made with good intentions even if they are wrong (excluding obvious vandalism) likewise if your edits are reverted please assume that it was for a good reason if you are not sure it’s always best to ask be respectful users should be civil to one another absolutely no sexist homophobic racist or any other derogatory remarks targeted towards any group of people are permitted basically be a decent human being do not engage with trolls occasionally there may be a problem user who will vandalize pages and leave derogatory comments and messages while it’s understandably tempting to engage with this person it is preferred that this user is ignored undo any vandalism the user may have caused and alert an admin immediately profiles and user content users are free to customize their profiles as they see fit as long as the content doesnt conflict with the rules on this page no sexual or explicit content will be permitted fan content is only allowed on user profiles before uploading fan content that you did not create yourself get permission from the original creator if you have discovered that something you created is being used without your consent please contact a member of the wikis staff and the file in question will be removed any files that break the rules will be deleted without warning however the user will be notified that the file was deleted as well as the reason why do not edit another users profile without their permission if a users profile content does not follow these guidelines please contact an admin editing users are expected to follow the wiki’s editing policies please see the [[stranger things wiki:style guide|style guide]] and [[stranger things wiki:layout guide|layout guide]] for the complete explanation of editing policies edits should be constructive and made with the purpose of improving an article’s content do not engage in edit wars instead discuss with other users or the wiki’s staff to find a solution do not vandalize the articles you will be blocked you have been warned article comments all comments under an article’s comment section should pertain to that article in some way inappropriate comments and comments containing spam will be removed discussion board the discussion board’s guidelines can also be found [https://strangerthingsfandomcom/d/g here] be nice and treat people with respect keep discussions civil and be openminded about differing opinions threads and posts that solicit upvotes will be deleted offtopic conversations will be deleted impersonation of other users or famous people will not be tolerated if you have been banned and return on a new account your posts will be deleted and your new account(s) will be banned no sharing personal information about yourself or other people no posts about people not involved with stranger things spamming trolling or vandalizing of any kind will be deleted and will lead to your account being banned posts made with the sole purpose of spreading false information will be deleted the report feature is for posts and comments that break the guidelines on this page do not report posts simply because you dont like them or for having an opinion you dont agree with [[category:templates]]|

|what makes an antagonist? what makes an antagonist? is lucas an antagonist for getting into a fight with mike? is lonnie an antagonist for being a deadbeat? is joyces boss an antagonist for almost denying her advances on her paycheck? is mr scotts date an antagonist for giving him the cold shoulder? maybe brenner has ends that justify the means is the monster truly an antagonist or is it just eating to survive? calling someone an antagonist is purely a subjective moral judgement in some cases im not sure its a valid category and theres definitely not a unifying factor about everyone being called an antagonist here that ties them together which is kinda the point of a category [[w:user:fishtank|fishtank]] ([[w:message wall:fishtank|wall]]) 03:07 september 1 2016 (utc)|

|what makes an antagonist? what makes an antagonist? is lucas an antagonist for getting into a fight with mike? is lonnie an antagonist for being a deadbeat? is joyces boss an antagonist for almost denying her advances on her paycheck? is mr scotts date an antagonist for giving him the cold shoulder? maybe brenner has ends that justify the means is the monster truly an antagonist or is it just eating to survive? calling someone an antagonist is purely a subjective moral judgement in some cases im not sure its a valid category and theres definitely not a unifying factor about everyone being called an antagonist here that ties them together which is kinda the point of a category [[w:user:fishtank|fishtank]] ([[w:message wall:fishtank|wall]]) 03:07 september 1 2016 (utc) : i vote to keep in this case its not a purely subjective moral judgement but rather explains the characters function in the story is brenner pure evil? is the monster? perhaps not but thats not what the term means in the context of narrative it just means that theyre the opposition the ones who stand in the way of the protagonists reaching their goal stranger things is a story that distinguishes between the protagonists and antagonists very clearly in my opinion [[user:80xpd|80xpd]] ([[user talk:80xpd|talk]]) 15:44 september 1 2016 (utc)|

|what makes an antagonist? what makes an antagonist? is lucas an antagonist for getting into a fight with mike? is lonnie an antagonist for being a deadbeat? is joyces boss an antagonist for almost denying her advances on her paycheck? is mr scotts date an antagonist for giving him the cold shoulder? maybe brenner has ends that justify the means is the monster truly an antagonist or is it just eating to survive? calling someone an antagonist is purely a subjective moral judgement in some cases im not sure its a valid category and theres definitely not a unifying factor about everyone being called an antagonist here that ties them together which is kinda the point of a category [[w:user:fishtank|fishtank]] ([[w:message wall:fishtank|wall]]) 03:07 september 1 2016 (utc) : i vote to keep in this case its not a purely subjective moral judgement but rather explains the characters function in the story is brenner pure evil? is the monster? perhaps not but thats not what the term means in the context of narrative it just means that theyre the opposition the ones who stand in the way of the protagonists reaching their goal stranger things is a story that distinguishes between the protagonists and antagonists very clearly in my opinion [[user:80xpd|80xpd]] ([[user talk:80xpd|talk]]) 15:44 september 1 2016 (utc) : i vote to keep as well for more or less the same reason as 80xpd: an antagonist is generally a character that functions as an obstacle that the protagonist needs to overcome and the division between protagonists and antagonists in stranger things are pretty clear cut the fact that you can justify the actions of an antagonist and maybe even sympathize with them does not make them any less of an antagonist it just makes for better storytelling (as does protagonists not always getting along as in the case with lucas) [[user:savemejebus|savemejebus]] ([[user talk:savemejebus|talk]]) 08:26 september 5 2016 (utc)|

page_ns: a Petition and a Fanfiction for Stranger Things.|
column10: |now before you go on judging me let me tell you this did not happen overnight this all took place at the end of 2017 when my brother and i finished watching stranger things (both seasons) somewhere in december after finishing it i kept having this thought in my mind that the hawkins lab test subjects are all female and none of then are in antagonistic roles (eight is an antihero which is a far cry from antagonist) then i started creating this character who is test subject male with a god complex and he is an antagonist but how do i make him stand out? by taking the very similarity they have their nosebleeding tens nose doesnt bleed because he uses a drug that inhibits that part of his brain for certain amount of time and if he doesnt take it soon then his entire face will bleed (so you can say he is a drug addict) with this idea exploding in my head everyday i decided to use it to my advantage thanks to a suggestion of my brother i created a petition regarding it (i do not care if they use it or not as long as i get noticed by st cast and crew) and it is currently sitting on over a 1000 signattures i also wrote a fanfiction using that character here are the links so do check them out changeorg petition link: https://wwwchangeorg/p/strangerthingscastcrewimadeafanmadecharacterfornetflixoriginalseriesstrangerthings wattpad fanfcition link: https://wwwwattpadcom/story/184001188strangerthingsten%27sascension [[category:blog posts]]|

page_title: |User blog:AbdullahBD02/Murray Bauman may play Cupid for Mileven for Season 4|
edit_content: |in the last episode of season 3 we dont see el and mike breaking up (because el done that in the second episode) but rather we see her telling him "i love you too" but that was before she read the hearttoheart speech by hopper and bursting into tears (+ the fact that she is moving out with the byers and leaving her friends behind in hawkins) in season 4 if the mind flayer (or the demogorgon) returns and the kids go through hell in hawkins for another time then el and mike may have second thoughts about their relationships el doesnt want to continue her relationship with mike fearing that he will put himself in danger for her and hurt or kill himself in the process and mike because she has already went through an emotional rollercoaster (not a real one though) last season because of losing hopper and he cannot for the second time this happens as a result they may try to put a halt in their relationship but have no fear as our favorite pi/conspiracy theorist/parttime cupid comes to their rescue he will probably do what he did with jancy and jopper to mileven and fix it which will lead it from them breaking upo to making up what do you think? [[category:blog posts]]|

|this is my theory for the entire 4th season in season 3 we saw hopper get blown up eleven losing her powers and flash forward to october 1985 we see the byers move out with eleven somewhere far away with promises of visiting each other on the holidays then jump to kamchatka russia and we see two guards drag a prisoner towards a fully grown demogorgon and they also have an american prisoner many have theorized that hopper is that american prisoner and some has also theorized that its actually brenner and hopper is either dead or stuck in the upside down (judging by the ladder near the machine which was on hoppers side) i personally want to believe all of them (except for hopper dead theory) and i have theorized how the next season (stranger things 4) might go (which also includes all the theories mentioned above except for hopper dead theory) heres how i think el will get back her powers it will probably happen because of will hear me out will got stuck in the upside down and had formed a connection with the mind flayer because of eleven now that hopper is (supposedly) dead joyce took in eleven in her family and moved far away from hawkins therefore eleven and will will form some kind of brothersister bond and because of that bond they will have the need to protect each other if one of the bullies in their new school thinks (i hope) will is gay then they would probably get a beating somewhere in front el and she unable to help will feel a strong emotion of anger and sadness and suddenly her powers reawakened this could also begin with a little hint where el is constantly having dreams of hopper being in a russian prison with russian guards or hiding in the upside down against the demogorgon of course when she tells joyce about it she passes it off as a nightmare by the end of first episode she reawakens her power and the first thing she does is to see whether her visions of hopper were dream or not and surprisingly she finds them to be true they return to hawkins after the incident of elevens power to cool it off and eleven mentions it to everyone thus the entire season will go on finding and saving hopper from either the russian prison or the upside down if hopper is in the upside down then she might find brenner in the russian prison what do you think about my st4 theory? [[category:blog posts]]|

page_title: |User blog:AbdullahBD02/My Theory on how the Russians got their own Demogorgon|
edit_content: |at the end of season 3 we saw hopper going off at an explosion but we didnt see him going off as he disappeared from the machine by the intervals of frames then flash forward to 3 months later october 1985 in kamchatka russia we see a couple of russian guards open a cell to take out a prisoner for some reason and before one of the guards could open the door the other guard told him "no not the american" and opened the door right next to that dragged the prisoner behind that door to somewhere and finally we get a glimpse of russians very own demogorgon but how did they got it? this has something to do with "hopper is alive" theory hear me out at 4th of july 1985 when the machine went off and hopper was on the wrong side of the machine so he couldnt go back to joyce and she had no choice but to turn the key to destroy the machine if you havent noticed there was a ladder right next to where hopper was standing so when joyce turned the key hopper noticed the ladder climbed down and having no choice went through the portal believing that el will find him but instead he got stuck in there for the duffers know how long meanwhile the russians once again tried to open the portal back in russia and probably succeeded and from there hopper got out and demogorgon was probably chasing him thus the russians caught two birds with one stone and if youre asking about the 10 feet tall cage erica found on episode 6 the russians probably anticipated that there was some kind of monsters behind the gate and kept it as precaution or brenner what do you think? [[category:blog posts]]|

edit_content: |so my theory is a big one so yeah get a bag of popcorn my theory is that whats her name hoppers daughter we are just gonna call her sara cause i feel like thats her name anyway i think that sara is part of mkultra because when we see clips of her she is fine then she stops so what if she can see into the upside down? it was a bit like will now also in the hospital/evil lab we see her um supposedly die i dont think that happened because kali can make people see things so what if she made hopper and his wife see that also because like come on that is not 11 in the rainbow room i also think that jane is sara because terry goes into the rainbow room and reaches for the blonde haired girl/sara then i think that she was connected not once when she had the um pleasure of going into the upside down she took her tiger and was there with will in the library but she was dead i think that we need to know more about the wonderful child sara by eggoeleven11 😀 [[category:blog posts]]|

edit_content: |i was recently looking into parallel universes on [https://enwikipediaorg/wiki/parallel_universe_(fiction) wikipedia] and came across an interesting correlation between stranger things and such eventually the page got to parallel universes within fantasy and mentioned a book written by a man named "john myers myers" and noticed how similiar this is to "jonathan byers " said book "[https://enwikipediaorg/wiki/silverlock silverlock] " is about a man who ventures to a mythical land full of mythical creatures drawn from history one can say that this land "the commonwealth of letters" is another fantasy version similiar to parallel universes seen as well with [[the upside down]] that being why it is mentioned within the article although i doubt the name is inspired from this author i found it very interesting and thought id share it with you guys perhaps it could be added to the notes of the [[jonathan byers]] page [[category:blog posts]]|

page_title: |User blog:FoolioMagizooligist/My Theories on How the Russians Got Their Own Demogorgon|
edit_content: |warning: major season 3 spoilers ahead: scroll down only if you have seen season 3 at the end of season 3 we saw jim hopper supposedly die but in the postcredit scene we saw a russian prison where one of the guards said "no not the american" the jim hopper is alive" theory is a whole other story though in that same russian prison a prisoner got taken way down the stairs where he got left with a demogorgon i have 3 theories on how that demogorgon got there and i listed them from least likely to most likely: it was the same demogorgon eleven defeated in season 1 eleven defeated the demogorgon in the classroom and they both turned to ash and died right? wrong as revealed in season 2 eleven was alive and found her way back to the real world from the upside down could this have happened to the demogorgon too? eleven was shown waking up in the upside down so its possible that the demogorgon could have too the stage 5 demodog that eleven killed and that dustin put in the byers fridge somehow survived or was brought back to life morphed into a stage six demogorgon and somehow got to the russian prison this one makes a little more sense than the last one even though the gate was closed the demodog was put in the fridge before it closed the monsters and vines and probably everything from the upside down hates and is discomforted hurt or even killed by heat the demodog was put in the cold fridge so the coldness being benificial to most upside down creatures health could have kept it alive or even revived it somehow if this is true then dustin may have screwed everyone for a (hopefully) upcoming season 4 my third theory and probably the most likely is that russia succeeded in opening the gate again and captured a demogorgon this would make sense because of another theory of mine which isnt really a theory it just makes sense for common knowledge: there is a whole world of the upside down not just hawkins there are probably a lot more monsters we dont know about different species of demogorgon and probably a whole lot of demogorgons scattered all over the place my guess is that the russians used the machine went into the upside down and captured and brought the demogorgon to one of their prisons or maybe all demogorgons would also be a good addition to their military if they could find a way to train them very likely at an early stage they probably would have caught the demogorgon at an early stage such as slug pollywog or frogogorgon if they were smart this in my opinion is the best theory that i have and maybe the best theory ever (just kidding) let me know what you think [[category:blog posts]]|

edit_content: |[[file:placeholder|video|right|300px]] [[file:screen_shot_20190713_at_94716_pmpng|thumb|the moon over weathertop ]][[file:screen_shot_20190713_at_94500_pmpng|thumb|the moon as hooper and joyce leave the fun fair]] write the first paragraph of your page here calendar season three the events of season 3 of stranger things revolves around the forth of july 1985 [[file:screen_shot_20190713_at_100953_pmpng|thumb|what phase is the moon?]]the moon phase and what day of the week is the climax? in the climax of this series the moon appears to be just off full or perhaps three quarters full during the fun fair according to [https://mooncalendarastroseekcom/moonphaseday6july1985 this source] on the full moon was the 2nd july in 1985 on the 4th july is was a waning gibbous moon (just off full) the forth of july in 1985 fell on a thursday was the fun fair held on the thursday itself or the saturday? the phase of the moon may give this away what do you think is it 2 or 4 days off full? the best look at the moon is at 17:56 and 36:11 in episode 8 the question is what day of the week is the climax held? is it the actual 4th july a thursday or the saturday after perhaps? maybe you noticed some other clues other then the phase of the moon in this scene suzies says she hasnt heard from dustin in a week this gives us some idea of the timline anyone have any more to contribute of this topic?|

|this is my review to the crtically acclaim stranger things 2/ stranger things season 2: stranger things 2 has definitely upped both the horifying aspect and the scale from the 1st season and is fittingly a massive improvement it has features some fantastic character development to most kids who were a bit left out in season 1 the duffer brothers have done a great job giving noah schnapp the role of will as he is still suffering from the consequences of the demogorgon and the way he shows his fear and pain is really fascinating millie bobby brown and david harbour as eleven and jim hopper respectively has also acted really well portraying the dynamic bond the duo made as they face newer challenges from the beginning the vfx team has also added a lot of visual aspects that make the atmosphere of hawkins and the creatures look more alive as well as frightening its just the definitive sequel one can only hope from such a tv series and thats without saying how the final act of the last episode "the gate" was so charming (most memorable scene) which without spoiling is hard to explain though season 2 has been superb it is not completely flawless at few aspects because the episode "the lost sister" broke the pace and tension a bit that rose from the previous episode "the spy" as it mostly focuses on eleven and her unexpected journey overall i would highly recommend any stranger things fan to watch it as it is both heartbreaking and also very memorable my overall rating: 95/10 [[file:mike_is_surprised_to_see_elevenpng|thumb|left|196px]] in any case this is just my review from my perspective and so sound off your opinions in the comments below [[category:blog posts]]|

edit_content: |al for him the d and d game in the first episode may have predicted this mike even tells lucas that will put himself at risk to save the party both acted very et harry potter frodo baggins jean grey leia or original trilogy luke skywalker like in their actions all of those characters took actions that they knew could cost them their lives to save the people they cared about if this theory that i have that i dont actually believe turns out to be true it would make will and eleven the luke and leia of stranger things it makes the theory seem to fall on some very cliched tropes but hey: its not like stranger things would ever ever ever ever ever ever ever in a million years reference star wars (or xmen or lord of the rings) right? whatever happens i do think that theres a team up coming soon between eleven and will soon mike did get caught by one on the tendrils in the tunnel so maybe theyll have to work together to save him (mike is the sam to wills frodo and the steve to wills bucky as well as the scott to elevens jean or the han to elevens leia) dustin and hopper both inhaled upside down dandruff so they may start spouting the spores describe in the montauk pilot [[category:blog posts]]|

page_title: |User blog:Josabby/Eleven and Will theory (that I don't actually believe)|
edit_content: |as discussed earlier in mikes identical reaction to them and rebirths through a portal from the upside down will had to be revived by joyce and hopper when they found him with a parasite (umbilical chord perhaps? totally reaching here i know) attached to him they presumably carried him back through the gate when they brought him back to our dimension eleven was at least briefly unconscious after her apparent death she literally crawled back through a placenta like portal into hawkins middle school both eleven and will demonstrate a willingness to sacrifice their own lives to save the people they care about eleven saying goodbye to mike before vanquishing the demogorgan indicates that she believed she was about to die (that was the intention when it was just going to be a mini series) this next part is speculation but mike realized that closing the gate would kill will if he was still connected to the hive mind if mike figured that out will must have known that as well once the shadow monster infected him he did "just know things" its not a stretch to conclude that will knew closing the gate would be fatal for him the d and d game in the first episode may have predicted this mike even tells lucas that will put himself at risk to save the party both acted very et harry potter frodo baggins jean grey leia or original trilogy luke skywalker like in their actions all of those characters took actions that they knew could cost them their lives to save the people they cared about if this theory that i have that i dont actually believe turns out to be true it would make will and eleven the luke and leia of stranger things it makes the theory seem to fall on some very cliched tropes but hey: its not like stranger things would ever ever ever ever ever ever ever in a million years reference star wars (or xmen or lord of the rings) right?
